The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Good Morning

 Hello It's Sunday, July 22, 2007

 Gadgets galore

 Drop in at Gadgetise, a gadgets and lifestyle exhibition presented by t2 and Exhibit magazine, at The Park, 10am to 8pm.

 On stage

 Enjoy Ho Sakta Hai Do Aadmi Do Kursiyaan at Padatik Little Theatre, 7pm.

 Harry Potter

 Spin your own Harry Potter yarn contest and games and tattoos at MamaMia! at Ballygunge and Alipore outlets, 1pm to 11.30pm

 Kitchen Fair

 Check out Kitchenex 2007 at Ice Skating Rink, noon to 8pm.

 Folk dance

 Watch Sankhabadan folk dance of Orissa, as a part of Orissa Festival by Utkala, at Swabhumi, 7pm. 

 Grand prix

 Be there at Speed Nights, screening of the German Grand Prix 2007, at Big Ben, The Kenilworth, 4.30pm.

 Eye camp

 Dhrishti 2007, eye camp organised by alumni associations of various schools and an NGO, at Blooming Buds School, 16 Sandal Street, 8am.

 Eye on Art

 Browse through an exhibition of paintings by The Find at Academy of Fine Arts (Central Gallery), 3pm to 8pm. 

 Drop in at an exhibition of paintings by Nibedita Sen and Rana Roy at Chemould, 10am to 7pm. 

 Move on to an exhibition of collages by Ranjan Sarkar at Chirakoot Art Gallery, 3pm to 8pm.

 Stop over at Svikriti at Birla Academy of Art and Culture, 3pm to 8pm. 




